description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INsmh, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: This Guy’s Revenge on a Noisy Neighbor Is So Petty, It Actually Worked
items.description: This guy's neighbor had his dog barking every night/morning at 3am, and when asked to do something about it, he laughed and did nothing. So, this man flipped the script and recorded the nightly yapping. He would then play the recording back, blasting it at full volume at his neighbor's house until dawn. No yelling, no door-slamming, just a little taste of his own medicine served through a speaker. By day three, the dog was tucked in like a toddler at bedtime. Who knew petty could be so peaceful?

items.title: They Built What in the Alps?!
items.description: Tor Alva, the world’s tallest 3D-printed building, standing proud in Mulegns—population: 12. Why there? Because when you’re trying to save a dying town, why not start with a techno-art tower made of printed spaghetti columns, giant screws, and zero steel? Swiss engineers claim it’s safe, sustainable, and portable—like IKEA furniture for giants. Locals got so hyped, 300 of them showed up (where did they all come from?), climbed to the top, and took in the view like it was the Eiffel Tower. SMH.
